<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-317-024  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 317 024.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  April 9 1990 n1402* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Japanese versions of Sun Office Publishing range ship next month.andO;(May 1990) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sun Microsystems Inc. (product introduction)Island Graphics Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    SUNW.andO;Product:   Sunwrite (Word processing software) (product introduction)Sundraw (Computer graphics software) (product introduction)Sunpaint (Computer graphics software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     JapanGraphics SoftwareWord Processing SoftwareMarketing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>JAPANESE VERSIONS OF SUN OFFICE PUBLISHING RANGEandM;SHIP NEXT MONTHandM;Japanese versions of the Sun Microsystems SunWrite, SunPaint and SunDrawrange of office publishing software are now ready, and will begin shippingnext month, according to Sun and its software partner Island Graphics Corp ofSan Rafael, California.andP;  The products, which run under the Open Lookgraphical user interface, were translated by Tokyo-based Unisol Corp, whichwill license them in Japan through its distribution channels: Unisol isjointly-owned by Fuji Xerox and Sun.andP;  Originally developed by IslandGraphics, and first introduced in February 1989, the packages are now said tobe the best-selling office software on Sun workstations.andP;  According to Unisoldirector of marketing and sales Michael Takahisa, they fill a gap in theJapanese marketplace: &quot;a middle solution between the limited PC-based wordprocessing and few very expensive technical publishing programs currentlyavailable&quot;, he said.andP;  Kanji and Kana characters are supported by the threeproducts, with the help of Sun's Japanese Language Environment.andP;  Prices willbe equivalent to the English versions, and programs run on Sun-3, Sun-4 andthe Sparcstation line.andP;  SunWrite is a WYSIWIG word processor or memos,letters and reports; SunPaint a raster graphics editor for scanned ororiginal images; and SunDraw a vector graphics editor for designs andillustrations.andO;</TEXT></DOC>